  "prompt": "When will we lose muscle mass in our body?",
  "response": "Muscle mass loss, or sarcopenia, is a condition that typically starts occurring gradually as part of the natural aging process, often beginning in one's 30s. Factors influencing the rate and extent of muscle mass loss include:\n\n1. **Age**: Muscle mass generally starts declining around the age of 30 and accelerates after the age of 50. \n2. **Physical Activity**: Sedentary lifestyles contribute to muscle loss, while regular exercise, especially resistance training, can help maintain muscle mass.\n3. **Diet**: Insufficient protein and calorie intake can lead to muscle deterioration. Adequate nutrition is crucial for muscle maintenance.\n4. **Hormonal Changes**: Changes in hormone levels, such as decreased levels of testosterone and estrogen, can affect muscle mass.\n5. **Chronic Illnesses**: Conditions like diabetes, heart disease, and chronic inflammation can contribute to sarcopenia.\n6. **Genetics**: Genetic predispositions may affect the rate of muscle decline.\n\nWhile muscle mass loss is part of aging, adopting a healthy and active lifestyle can slow its progression. Regular strength training exercises, balanced nutrition, and overall health management are key strategies.",
